  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help us help Nature restore the Pterocarpus Forest</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2 1/2 years after Hurricane Maria devastated Puerto Rico and the rare Pterocarpus Forest at Palmas del Mar, the rebirth of the forest has taken place, slowly, naturally.  It&apos;s canopy remains severley damaged, leading to the growth of strange species. Rather than rely on nature alone, the Friends of the Forest want to deliberately plant 50 new, native trees, including the critical Pterocarpus, to spur reforestation and to spur the restoration of the canopy.</narrative>
  </description>
